---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const pageSchema = JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Service",
  "name": "Guillotine Glass Windows Spain",
  "description": "Motorised guillotine glass windows for terraces and apartments in Spain. Vertical lift glass panels with panoramic views. Supplied by Costa Glass.",
  "provider": { "@type": "LocalBusiness", "name": "Costa Glass", "url": "https://costaglass.com" },
  "url": "https://costaglass.com/en/guillotine-glass-windows/"
});
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Guillotine Glass Windows Spain | Motorised Vertical Glass | Costa Glass"
  description="Guillotine glass windows for Spanish terraces and sea-view apartments. Electric vertical-lift glass panels, no visible frames, panoramic views. Costa Glass specialists."
  canonical="https://costaglass.com/en/guillotine-glass-windows/"
  ogImage="https://costaglass.com/Assets/products/Guillotine-Style Glass Windows/download.webp"
  pageSchema={pageSchema}
  lang="en"
>

<style>
  .en-hero { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f172a 0%, #1c1917 100%); color: white; padding: 100px 20px 80px; text-align: center; }
  .en-hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.2rem); margin: 0 0 20px; font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; }
  .en-hero p { font-size: 1.2rem; max-width: 650px; margin: 0 auto 32px; opacity: 0.9; }
  .en-badge { display: inline-block; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3); border-radius: 30px; padding: 6px 20px; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .en-section { padding: 70px 20px; }
  .en-section:nth-child(even) { background: #f8fafc; }
  .en-container { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .en-section h2 { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.2rem); color: #0f172a; margin: 0 0 24px; font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; }
  .en-section p { font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; color: #374151; margin: 0 0 18px; }
  .use-cases { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin: 28px 0; }
  .use-case { background: white; border-radius: 12px; padding: 22px; border-top: 4px solid #0f172a; border-left: 1px solid #e2e8f0; border-right: 1px solid #e2e8f0; border-bottom: 1px solid #e2e8f0; }
  .use-case h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 10px; }
  .use-case p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: #475569; margin: 0; }
  .price-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 24px 0; }
  .price-table th { background: #0f172a; color: white; padding: 12px 16px; text-align: left; }
  .price-table td { padding: 12px 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid #e2e8f0; color: #374151; }
  .price-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: #f8fafc; }
  .cta-band { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f172a, #1e293b); color: white; padding: 60px 20px; text-align: center; }
  .cta-band h2 { font-size: 2rem; margin: 0 0 16px; }
  .cta-band p { font-size: 1.1rem; margin: 0 0 28px; opacity: 0.95; max-width: 560px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; }
  .btn-white { display: inline-block; background: white; color: #0f172a; padding: 14px 32px; border-radius: 8px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem; }
  .btn-white:hover { background: #f1f5f9; }
  .related-links { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 20px 0 0; display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 12px; }
  .related-links a { display: inline-block; background: #f1f5f9; color: #374151; padding: 8px 18px; border-radius: 6px; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 500; }
  .timeline { margin: 28px 0; }
  .timeline-item { display: flex; gap: 16px; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .timeline-dot { width: 36px; height: 36px; border-radius: 50%; background: #0f172a; color: white; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; }
  .timeline-content h3 { margin: 0 0 4px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem; }
  .timeline-content p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; color: #475569; }
</style>

<section class="en-hero">
  <div class="en-container">
    <span class="en-badge">Motorised Vertical Glass</span>
    <h1>Guillotine Glass Windows Spain</h1>
    <p>The guillotine glass system — panels that lift vertically and disappear into a hidden overhead cassette — delivers a completely unobstructed opening without a single profile in the view.</p>
    <a href="/contact" class="btn-white">Get a Free Quote</a>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- How it works -->
<section class="en-section">
  <div class="en-container">
    <h2>How Guillotine Glass Windows Work</h2>
    <p>A guillotine glass window — known as <em>ventana guillotina de cristal</em> in Spanish — operates on a vertical-lift principle. A single large panel of toughened glass (typically 10 mm or 12 mm thick) slides vertically upward within a pair of slim side channels and parks inside a slim cassette housing at the top of the opening. When fully raised, the glass panel is completely hidden in the overhead housing, leaving the opening entirely clear — no glass, no frame, just open air.</p>
    <p>The lifting mechanism is electric, operated by a wall switch, remote control, or smartphone app. The motor system uses a counterweight or gas-strut assist to reduce power consumption and allow manual override in the event of a power failure. The system can be fitted with sensors to close automatically when rain is detected.</p>
    <p>Unlike glass curtain systems — which fold panels to the side — the guillotine system is ideal for openings where there is no side space for stacking panels. A perfect example is a top-floor penthouse terrace where the side walls are occupied by structural columns, or a sea-view apartment where every centimetre of side wall is occupied by decking or furniture.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Ideal use cases -->
<section class="en-section">
  <div class="en-container">
    <h2>Ideal Use Cases for Guillotine Glass in Spain</h2>
    <p>Guillotine glass windows are not the right solution for every situation — but where they fit, they are transformative. Here are the scenarios where our Costa del Sol clients consistently choose guillotine glass over alternative systems.</p>

    <div class="use-cases">
      <div class="use-case">
        <h3>Penthouse Terraces</h3>
        <p>Top-floor apartments with no side wall space for folding panels. The cassette sits above and out of sight, leaving the full opening clear.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="use-case">
        <h3>Sea-View Balconies</h3>
        <p>Where preserving the view is the absolute priority. When the panel is raised, nothing obstructs the panorama — not even the narrow channel guides at the sides.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="use-case">
        <h3>Restaurant Terraces</h3>
        <p>A single 3-metre wide guillotine panel can open an entire restaurant frontage in 10 seconds, effortlessly transitioning between enclosed and al fresco dining.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="use-case">
        <h3>Pool Houses & Cabanas</h3>
        <p>A full-width opening between pool and interior creates the seamless indoor-outdoor flow that defines luxury Costa del Sol living.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Price guide -->
<section class="en-section">
  <div class="en-container">
    <h2>Guillotine Glass Price Guide (Spain, 2025)</h2>
    <p>Guillotine glass systems are premium products, priced above standard glass curtain systems due to the engineering complexity of the vertical-lift mechanism and the larger glass panels required. Prices below are for fully motorised systems including manufacture, delivery, and installation in the Málaga province.</p>

    <table class="price-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Panel Width</th><th>Glass Thickness</th><th>Estimated Price</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Up to 1.5 m wide</td><td>10 mm</td><td>€2,800 – €4,500</td></tr>
        <tr><td>1.5–2.5 m wide</td><td>10 mm</td><td>€4,000 – €6,500</td></tr>
        <tr><td>2.5–3.5 m wide</td><td>12 mm</td><td>€5,500 – €9,000</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Multiple panels</td><td>12 mm</td><td>Price per panel × n</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>Installation of a guillotine glass window typically takes one full day per panel. Unlike glass curtain systems, guillotine panels require a prepared overhead housing, which may involve minor carpentry or masonry work at the top of the opening. Costa Glass coordinates all associated trades and manages the complete installation.</p>

    <h2>Installation Timeline</h2>
    <div class="timeline">
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-dot">1</div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <h3>Free Site Survey</h3>
          <p>We assess the opening dimensions, wall construction, and overhead space available for the cassette housing.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-dot">2</div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <h3>Design & Fabrication</h3>
          <p>Custom cassette and glass panel manufactured in Estepona. Lead time approximately 4–6 weeks from order confirmation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-dot">3</div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <h3>Installation</h3>
          <p>1–2 days on-site. Cassette installed first, then glass panel fitted and electrical connection made. Full function testing before handover.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-dot">4</div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <h3>Handover & Warranty</h3>
          <p>Full demonstration of operation. 2-year mechanical warranty included. Glass covered by manufacturer guarantee.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <ul class="related-links">
      <li><a href="/guillotina-de-cristal">View Guillotine Glass product page →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/en/frameless-glass-enclosures">Frameless Glass Enclosures →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/en/glass-curtains-marbella">Glass Curtains Marbella →</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="cta-band">
  <h2>Enquire About Guillotine Glass for Your Property</h2>
  <p>Contact Costa Glass for a free site assessment. We'll advise whether a guillotine system is the right solution and provide a detailed quotation.</p>
  <a href="/contact" class="btn-white">Request a Free Quote</a>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
